_Proof._ Since \(\bm{v}^{*}\) is an accumulation point of \(\{\bm{v}^{(k)}\}_{k\in\mathbb{N}}\), there exists a subsequence \(\{\bm{v}^{(k_{j})}\}_{j\in\mathbb{N}_{+}}\) of \(\{\bm{v}^{(k)}\}_{k\in\mathbb{N}}\) such that \(\lim_{j\to\infty}\bm{v}^{(k_{j})}=\bm{v}^{*}\). Note that the set \(\Omega\) is closed and \(\bm{v}^{(k_{j})}\in\Omega\) for all \(j\in\mathbb{N}_{+}\). Hence \(\bm{v}^{*}\in\Omega\), which completes the proof. 

