### Solving Algorithm: mSSRM-PGA

**Input:** Given the sample asset return matrix \(\bm{R}\in\mathbb{R}^{T\times N}\) and the positive parameter \(\epsilon\).

**Preparation:** Let \(\bm{p}=\frac{1}{T}\bm{R}^{\top}\bm{1}_{T}\), \(\bm{Q}=\frac{1}{\sqrt{T-1}}\left(\bm{R}-\frac{1}{T}\bm{1}_{T\times T}\bm{R}\right)\) and \(\bm{Q}_{\epsilon}=\bm{Q}^{\top}\bm{Q}+\epsilon\bm{I}\). Compute the largest eigenvalue \(\lambda_{1}\) of \(\bm{Q}_{\epsilon}\), and set \(\alpha=\frac{0.999}{\lambda_{1}}\).

**Initialization:** Set \(\bm{v}^{(0)}=\bm{p}\), \(tol=10^{-5}\), \(MaxIter=10^{4}\) and \(k=0\).

**repeat**

1. \(\bm{v}^{(k+1)}=\mathrm{prox}_{\iota_{\Omega}}\left(\bm{v}^{(k)}-\alpha\left( \bm{Q}_{\epsilon}\bm{v}^{(k)}-\bm{p}\right)\right)\)

2. \(k=k+1\)

**until \(\frac{\|\bm{v}^{(k)}-\bm{v}^{(k-1)}\|_{2}}{\|\bm{v}^{(k-1)}\|_{2}}\leqslant tol\)** or \(k>MaxIter\).

**if \(\bm{v}^{(k)}\neq\bm{0}_{N}\)**

3. \(\bm{w}^{*}=\frac{\bm{v}^{(k)}}{(\bm{v}^{(k)})^{\top}\bm{1}_{N}}\)

**else**

4. \(\bm{w}^{*}=\bm{0}_{N}\)

**Output:** The portfolio \(\bm{w}^{*}\).

**Algorithm A1** mSSRM-PGA

